description:
**ReachCentrum** was created in June 2006 by Cefic (the European Chemical Industry Council) to help companies all through the value chain to prepare and implement REACH and Biocides. Since 2015, ReachCentrum is owned by Environmental Resources Management (ERM), the world’s leading global provider of environmental, health, safety, risk, social consulting services and sustainability related services.


REACH is a European Union regulation adopted to protect human health and environment against the risks that chemical substances pose, and to improve the competitiveness of the chemical industry in the EU.


ReachCentrum’s professionals help businesses in the chemical industry navigate through the business implications of REACH, CLP and Biocides legislation and processes.


REACH mandates chemical companies to register their substances manufactured or imported in a joined effort with other potential registrants of the same substance. In order to prepare the necessary communication and decision making processes, companies organize themselves in REACH consortia.


Currently ReachCentrum is managing about 100 consortia, which require tailored advice on regulatory compliance at all stages of the REACH Regulation. To strengthen its expertise in the chemicals regulatory field and enhance the support provided to clients, ReachCentrum is seeking an experienced Consortia Project Manager to be part of its dynamic team.



As a **Project Manager,** you support Members by managing the entire administration and activities of the consortium. The aim of your role is to lead the project management of new and existing consortia, support projects and consultancy. Depending on the stage, this requires solid skills with respect to:

* project management
* executing administrative responsibilities and financial management
* ability to work on different projects in parallel
* ability to prioritize tasks and adjust the action plan continuously



ReachCentrum has extended its product portfolio over the past several years and is developing new services in relation to global REACH\-like regulations. You will contribute to the development of the services and the execution of the tasks. You will report to the General Manager or the ReachCentrum team lead and will be supported by ReachCentrum staff.



Additional requirements include:

* Negotiation skills;
* experience Collaborating and communicating with companies to advocate common\-interests;
* Adaptability to work on tight deadlines and handle multiple priorities.
* REACH expertise and knowledge of EU policy on Chemicals OR a strong interest in this area and the willingness and ability to learn quickly.
* Advanced understanding of competition law
* Advanced understanding of REACH related legal and contractual issues
* Interest in the project financial management and willingness to learn about complex cost sharing rules.

 **Main Tasks**

* Organize consortia activities;
* Maintain, communicate and manage the consortia planning;
* Maintain administration (including financial management) and organize communication with other stakeholders; facilitate consortia meetings both technical and executive ones
* Lead discussions and build consensus;
* Coordinate the ongoing technical work of the consortia;
* Prepare drafts of the legal documents when required, and flag potential legal issues before they become critical;
* Cooperate with the finance team to maintain the Consortia finances, by providing inputs on the Consortia specific rules and ongoing work
* Support clients in day\-to\-day REACH/biocides related business operations;
* Maintain contacts with third parties and authorities (ECHA, European Commission etc.) on behalf of clients;
* Knowledge of best practices and trends in regulatory management;
* Thought leadership: leading and acting on behalf of the client;
* Resolve challenges: solve clients’ concerns and create solutions for foreseeable issues;
* Insight on latest industry trends to present opportunities and avoid pitfalls;
* Advisor to client(s) about potential impact of the regulations, demonstrating foresight and contributing to his/her success;
* Recognize potential issues and propose viable solutions. Liaise with clients to generate creative solutions.

**Profile**


The ideal candidate will be an experienced professional who has:

* A master degree or equivalent;
* Solid knowledge of REACH and experience with European chemicals law (REACH, BPR and CLP);
* 5\-10 years of experience as project manager in a client facing role Consultancy skills and experience of working within a consulting (or similar) environment;
* Proven record of working with multiple stakeholders in joint projects where communication and decision making are critical;
* Effective communicator in English, active listener and excellent interpersonal skills;
* Experience advising clients on regulatory issues


⠀


ERM is committed to creating an inclusive workplace where everyone feels valued, respected, and empowered to thrive, it’s an essential part of what makes ERM a great place to build a career and helps us create better solutions for our clients.


We welcome talent from all backgrounds and provide equal opportunities for every candidate. If you have a disability, are neurodivergent, or need accommodations during the selection process, we’re here to support you. Our commitment doesn’t stop at hiring. Once you join us, we’ll ensure you have the tools, support, and adjustments needed to succeed and feel a true sense of belonging. Learn more about our Diversity, Inclusion \& Belonging (DIB) efforts by visiting our website or exploring our 2025 Sustainability Report..

Arcadis is the world's leading company delivering sustainable design, engineering, and consultancy solutions for natural and built assets.



We are more than 34,000 people, in over 30 countries, dedicated to improving quality of life. Everyone has an important role to play. With the power of many curious minds, together we can solve the world’s most complex challenges and deliver more impact together.


**Role description:**



Arcadis is looking for a skilled **Design Manager** that will join our team. You will be responsible for the technical coordination of interdisciplinary design team both from Arcadis and external parties like subcontractors' or client's.



You will also lead and integrate efforts across our international Arcadis Delivery Centers, ensuring the timely and efficient delivery of project milestones while maintaining the highest quality standards. You will maintain direct communication with clients and suppliers, managing expectations and activities.



The ideal candidate has already previous experience working in multinational companies and in the Data Center industry, in a BIM setting and with integrated design of building systems teams.


**Role accountabilities:**


* Management of coordination activities in a BIM environment, formulating inputs and observations on the ACC platform;
* Verification of the qualitative and quantitative technical contents of the design in relation to the project requirements in the various phases of work. Care of official deliveries to the customer;
* Punctual verification of the work carried out by external consultants through continuous contact with them and management of their invoices;
* Coordination of permitting activities and specialist consultancy to obtain building permits (the knowledge of environmental permits as well will be considered a plus);
* Preparation of summary reports relating to the various project phases for the company management;
* Management and monitoring of planning, verification, and control of the execution times of each activity, both for Arcadis teams and external suppliers;
* Collaboration with the field staff and / or with departmental colleagues to anticipate and resolve projects\-related problems;
* Collaboration with managers of various disciplines to maintain a strong team, cultivating the relationships between each specialist group and enhancing the work of each individual team member.


**Qualifications \& Experience:**


* At least **10 years of experience** in related fields;
* A **Degree in Mechanical, Civil/Building engineering** or a related sector;
* An **excellent level English** (**C1**) **,** and a **Good level of Italian (B1\)**;
* Good knowledge of single text of the legislative and regulatory provisions on construction in Italy, AutoCAD, Revit (Autodesk) and ACC work platform;
* Ability to travel autonomously;
* Knowledge and experience **in MEP and firefighting** disciplines will be considered a plus;
* Proven construction management experience in **Data Center** will be considered a plus;
* Good knowledge and experience with project management procedures will be considered a plus;
* **Frequent site presence will be required. Projects are based in Milan hinterland, mainly east and south of Milan**


Why Arcadis?



We can only achieve our goals when everyone is empowered to be their best. We believe everyone's contribution matters. It’s why we are pioneering a skills\-based approach, where you can harness your unique experience and expertise to carve your career path and maximize the impact we can make together.



You’ll do meaningful work, and no matter what role, you’ll be helping to deliver sustainable solutions for a more prosperous planet. Make your mark, on your career, your colleagues, your clients, your life and the world around you.



Together, we can create a lasting legacy.



Join Arcadis. Create a Legacy.



Our Commitment to Equality, Diversity, Inclusion \& Belonging



We want you to be able to bring your best self to work every day, which is why we take equality and inclusion seriously and hold ourselves to account for our actions. Our ambition is to be an employer of choice and provide a great place to work for all our people.



The annual salary range for this position is €50\.000,00 \- € 75\.000,00\.



\#LI\-GS1  

\#LI\-Onsite

Hairmed Experience ricerca un/a **Apprendista Senior Parrucchiere/a** da inserire nel proprio team presso il salone di **Via Farini 33, Milano**.

Cerchiamo una persona motivata, con esperienza già maturata in salone, desiderosa di crescere professionalmente in un ambiente dinamico, formativo e orientato all'eccellenza del servizio.

**Requisiti**

* Esperienza pregressa nel ruolo di apprendista parrucchiere/a;
* Buone competenze tecniche di base;
* Attitudine al lavoro di squadra e al contatto con il pubblico;
* Passione per il settore hair \& beauty;
* Voglia di mettersi in gioco e crescere professionalmente.

**Cosa offriamo**

* Contratto di apprendistato;
* Percorso strutturato di formazione e crescita professionale;
* Inserimento in un team qualificato e stimolante;
* Affiancamento continuo e possibilità di sviluppo di carriera.

**Retribuzione e incentivi**

* **Stipendio base: 1\.200 € netti al mese**;
* **Importante sistema di premi e incentivi legato al raggiungimento di obiettivi personali**;
* Possibilità concreta di raggiungere **fino a 1\.800 € netti al mese** al conseguimento dei risultati previsti.

**Orario di lavoro**

Dal martedì al sabato.

Se desideri entrare a far parte di un progetto in crescita e costruire il tuo futuro professionale nel mondo dell'haircare, inviaci la tua candidatura completa di CV.

Retribuzione: €1\.200,00 \- €1\.800,00 al mese

Benefit:

* Supporto allo sviluppo professionale

Sede di lavoro: Di persona

Polaris è stata fondata nel 1996 e sin dall’inizio l'azienda è cresciuta rapidamente e si è distinta per la capacità di studiare e realizzare processi con elevata complessità. Tra i principali clienti si possono elencare industrie chimiche e farmaceutiche tra le più prestigiose in Italia e nel mondo.

Nel 2008 è nato il Gruppo Polaris con la fusione con Delta, una società altamente qualificata nella progettazione e costruzione di attrezzature e sistemi per l'industria farmaceutica e chimica fine, e Kosmos, società specializzata nella costruzione di impianti industriali, servizi di manutenzione ordinaria e speciale in loco.

Per il potenziamento della struttura di Misinto, stiamo selezionando un/una **Service Technician** che verrà inserito/a nel team Service, un gruppo di lavoro che, all’interno della struttura Polaris, si occupa della gestione dei servizi post\-vendita che prevedono le seguenti attività:

· Supporto dei clienti da remoto per la gestione degli impianti installati presso gli stessi (troubleshooting ed ottimizzazione);

· Visite periodiche di ispezione e manutenzione presso gli impianti;

· Interventi di manutenzione straordinaria per: riparazioni; lavaggi o altre attività di natura straordinaria, modifiche o miglioramenti.

Il ruolo prevede lo svolgimento delle seguenti attività:

· Controllo, da remoto e non, della funzionalità degli impianti;

· Supporto al cliente da remoto e in sede per rilevamento problematiche;

· Organizzazione ed esecuzione di interventi di assistenza tecnica per manutenzioni programmate e non con l’aiuto di tecnici di campo;

· Gestione del rapporto con il cliente;

· Redazione di report di intervento e consuntivazione dell’intervento.

Si richiede:

· Diploma di Perito Elettronico o equipollente;

· Capacità di lettura del disegno tecnico e dello schema elettrico;

· Disponibilità a trasferte;

· Buona conoscenza della lingua inglese scritta e parlata;

· Preferibilmente 2 anni di esperienza nel ruolo.

Si offre: assunzione diretta, inquadramento e RAL commisurati all’esperienza maturata nel ruolo, (range ral € 27\.000 – 32\.000\), welfare, assicurazione sanitaria e buoni pasto da 8 € giornalieri. Orario di lavoro: dal Lunedì al Venerdì dalle 9 alle 18 con un’ora di pausa pranzo.

Gli annunci si rivolgono ai candidati di entrambi i sessi (Art. 27, comma 5, D. Lgs.198/06\) e ss.mm.ii. e dei Decreti Legislativi n. 215 e n. 216 del 2003 sulle parità di trattamento. Invitiamo a leggere l’informativa privacy ai sensi degli artt. 13 e 14 del Reg. EU 679/2016

Retribuzione: €27\.000,00 \- €32\.000,00 all'anno

Benefit:

* Buoni pasto

Istruzione:

* Scuola Secondaria di II livello (Superiori) (Obbligatorio)

Sede di lavoro: Di persona
